The paper deals with signal processing techniques for ultrasound imaging, which involves sampling and reconstruction of signals. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques for volumetric ultrasound imaging, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves simulation and experimentation with ultrasound data, which falls under statistical learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
